{"type":"message","id":"2ec38802","parentId":"0da660a4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:37:48.973Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_D99dGMKeOX7l7qak2GFO9S6l|fc_077585180826814c0169cc68d9f2c0819ab84d036347028756","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def main() -> None:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Generate same-day live smallcap candidates\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--date\", default=\"\", help=\"YYYYMMDD, default today\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--price-src\", default=str(DEFAULT_PRICE_CSV))\n    parser.add_argument(\"--basic-src\", default=str(DEFAULT_BASIC_CSV))\n    parser.add_argument(\"--config\", default=str(DEFAULT_CONFIG))\n    parser.add_argument(\"--main-output\", default=\"\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--guard-output\", default=\"\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--summary-output\", default=\"\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--main-count\", type=int, default=10)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--guard-count\", type=int, default=8)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--main-target-weight\", type=float, default=0.10)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--guard-target-weight\", type=float, default=0.08)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--overwrite\", action=\"store_true\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--max-price-lag-days\", type=int, default=3, help=\"价格源相对目标日允许的最大日历滞后\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--max-basic-lag-days\", type=int, default=7, help=\"daily_basic 相对目标日允许的最大日历滞后\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    date_tag = args.date.strip() or datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n    target_date = int(date_tag)\n    main_path = main_output_path(date_tag, args.main_output)\n    guard_path = guard_output_path(date_tag, args.guard_output)\n    summary_path = summary_output_path(date_tag, args.summary_output)\n\n    summary: dict[str, Any] = {\n        \"generated_at\": datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"),\n        \"date_tag\": date_tag,\n        \"target_trade_date\": date_tag,\n        \"price_src\": str(Path(args.price_src)),\n        \"basic_src\": str(Path(args.basic_src)),\n        \"config\": str(Path(args.config)),\n        \"market_trade_date\": \"\",\n        \"daily_basic_trade_date\": \"\",\n        \"outputs\": {},\n        \"top_preview\": {},\n        \"status\": \"PASS\",\n        \"reason\": \"\",\n    }\n\n    try:\n        cfg = load_smallcap_config(Path(args.config))\n        price_frame = load_price_history(Path(args.price_src), target_date)\n        universe, market_trade_date = build_market_snapshot(price_frame, cfg)\n        summary[\"market_trade_date\"] = market_trade_date\n\n        basic_trade_date, daily_basic = load_latest_daily_basic(Path(args.basic_src), target_date)\n        summary[\"daily_basic_trade_date\"] = basic_trade_date\n\n        price_lag_days = _calendar_lag_days(date_tag, market_trade_date)\n        basic_lag_days = _calendar_lag_days(date_tag, basic_trade_date)\n        summary[\"price_lag_days\"] = int(price_lag_days) if price_lag_days < 10**9 else None\n        summary[\"basic_lag_days\"] = int(basic_lag_days) if basic_lag_days < 10**9 else None\n        if price_lag_days > int(args.max_price_lag_days):\n            raise ValueError(f\"stale_price_source: market_trade_date={market_trade_date} lag_days={price_lag_days} target={date_tag}\")\n        if basic_trade_date and basic_lag_days > int(args.max_basic_lag_days):\n            raise ValueError(f\"stale_daily_basic_source: daily_basic_trade_date={basic_trade_date} lag_days={basic_lag_days} target={date_tag}\")\n\n        main_candidates = select_main_candidates(\n            universe,\n            limit=max(1, int(args.main_count)),\n            target_weight=max(0.0, float(args.main_target_weight)),\n        )\n        guard_candidates = build_guard_candidates(\n            universe,\n            daily_basic,\n            limit=max(1, int(args.guard_count)),\n            target_weight=max(0.0, float(args.guard_target_weight)),\n        )\n\n        summary[\"outputs\"][\"v4_2\"] = write_candidates(main_path, main_candidates, overwrite=bool(args.overwrite))\n        summary[\"outputs\"][\"v4_2b\"] = write_candidates(guard_path, guard_candidates, overwrite=bool(args.overwrite))\n        summary[\"top_preview\"][\"v4_2\"] = (\n            main_candidates[[\"ts_code\", \"score\"]].head(5).to_dict(orient=\"records\")\n            if not main_candidates.empty else []\n        )\n        summary[\"top_preview\"][\"v4_2b\"] = (\n            guard_candidates[[\"ts_code\", \"score\", \"guard_mode\"]].head(5).to_dict(orient=\"records\")\n            if not guard_candidates.empty else []\n        )\n        if not basic_trade_date:\n            summary[\"reason\"] = \"daily_basic_missing_guard_used_tech_fallback\"\n    except Exception as exc:\n        summary[\"status\"] = \"FAIL\"\n        summary[\"reason\"] = str(exc)\n        summary[\"outputs\"][\"v4_2\"] = {\"path\": str(main_path), \"status\": \"not_written\", \"rows\": count_csv_rows(main_path)}\n        summary[\"outputs\"][\"v4_2b\"] = {\"path\": str(guard_path), \"status\": \"not_written\", \"rows\": count_csv_rows(guard_path)}\n\n    ensure_parent(summary_path)\n    summary_path.write_text(json.dumps(summary, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(json.dumps(summary, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n\n[7 more lines in file. Use offset=450 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775003868968}}
{"type":"message","id":"747fc965","parentId":"2ec38802","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:40:46.639Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering data refresh options**\n\nI'm thinking about using the absence of daily_basic as a fallback if basic_trade_date is empty. However, if I do that, it seems like any stale data over 7 days would fail. I could increase the max-basic-lag-days for a temporary solution, but that wouldn't really provide an actual update. The user clearly wants updated data, which complicates things since they mentioned updating soon. It might be better to prepare some provisional data but, based on the developer's guidance, I can only generate real-time updates.\n\n**Planning data update process**\n\nI'm considering using the tushare daily_basic function to gather necessary fields for each trade date, like 'ts_code', 'close', and 'pe'. I'll need to load the token and possibly update the file, but that's internal and safe. To do this, I'll create a temporary script or run inline Python. \n\nI think I should set a timeout of around 180 seconds and use dotenv to manage environment files. I’ll get the latest trade date and determine the target, checking open days with trade_cal before appending the data and merging it all together. It should take about 16 days, which is manageable!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_077585180826814c0169cc6976aa74819aa7eb63db2f85d7fe\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpzGmB4J6nBaFUwAkvinOJpKuQmOrpJJzdiMHsMLAVzgwf7VO7ZaJk4_b5jbDdkXUsEe5LOIytAZzEoBFeyxoGZ9us0FWVeSRCmhhol_XN7GtrGhgvaRaIg4ura-tuO9gLXzplWcoOWZaahs8BvZV3jDzsymBTH29tzhztMOjgRQKnIqGWetsys7W-oVqLQu7YWPafMyxFohJq1DMpZTjiAu58tSGou3OvqUE84G2cRvA9PZ_WiBYS_qGpzDo8QMIKNNUJgxIfMZUCjwYkQud16sUqpz-sda2ZjsDqcqK3b8yUb7jX3HrTOPa2e9JG68IlMwfB1-_zbTKBUbORfBfdAW91V7gPAP1e2c5a_r5D95LKVUw-jUdw4_1KmSxIUfgkQEAhrtc4JWFCmUhdLkE_re_pwZLPSmLa3uOETQ0Ndo7dpPfBT-M2bwtVDszIvBLIAYeqf-KjTcC1eklcwnUcSLJXD43zSWVvW5ngSLyWpHr_C38TUP0dJ6wQ