{"type":"message","id":"c71172ca","parentId":"0293c213","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:24:54.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sync ran but still shows 23 holdings total and 诺思格 is still 400 shares. The system is still reading from the old `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.csv` which doesn't have the new 500 shares. This means the THS web source itself hasn't been updated with the new shares.\n\nThis is actually the core problem - the `ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.csv` is from an earlier snapshot and doesn't reflect today's new purchase of 500 shares of 诺思格.\n\nThe system needs to know that the user manually added 500 shares of 诺思格. I should:\n\n\n1. Tell the user that the system's holdings source (ths_web_selected_holdings_latest.csv) still shows 400 shares\n2. The system can't auto-detect the manual trade\n3. Either update the web holdings source, or use the THS skill to refresh the holdings\n\nI should now check if there's a way to directly update this with the new purchase information. The real issue is that the sync script is reading from the same stale file that doesn't reflect the new shares. I need to explore whether I can manually refresh the source or if the user needs to trigger a new sync through the THS interface.","thinkingSignature":"ef02a69645811f8d01807189ace0523ba33921417813b201f1d047c24f695361"},{"type":"text","text":"\n系统里的 THS 源还没有更新到那 500 股。我现在直接用 THS skill 抓你今天的真实账户。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f9ec6k24nwrj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nPYTHON = 'python3'\nskill_script = Path.home() / '.openclaw/skills/ths-local-holdings/scripts/ths_local_holdings.py'\nresult = Path('/tmp/ths_refresh_1610_result.json')\nimport subprocess, json\n\nr = subprocess.run(\n    [PYTHON, str(skill_script), 'sync', '--output', '/tmp/ths_refresh_1610'],\n    capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60\n)\nout = (r.stdout + r.stderr)[-2000:]\nprint(out)\nr