{"type":"message","id":"f7c936ca","parentId":"97d39d31","timestamp":"2026-04-01T08:37:02.681Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API returned 401 Unauthorized. This is because the cookies are not being sent properly with curl. The cookies contain session information that's needed for authentication, but when I use the `-H` flags to set headers manually, curl doesn't automatically include cookies unless I use the `-b` flag.\n\nLooking at the cookies from the user's request:\n```\n-H 'Cookie: Hm_lvt_78c58f01938e4d85eaf619eae71b4ed1=1772148277; u_ukey=A10702B8689642C6BE607730E11E6E4A; ...'\n\n\n```\n\nI need to either extract and pass the cookies with `-b` or use the `--cookie` option instead of setting them manually with `-H`. The auth headers like `u_name`, `userid`, and `ticket` are what's actually authenticating the request, so those need to be included properly in the cookie jar rather than as custom headers.\n\nThe session token in the cookies is probably expired or invalid. Since the request is returning 401 Unauthorized, I should save the cookies to a file and let curl handle them automatically instead of trying to pass them manually. The real issue might be that these cookies were revoked server-side, so even with the right format, the authentication fails. Since I can't get a fresh session, I'll focus on what I can do with the data I already have.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"199501d934f65e4f416bbb52a139a5511960242dca741ba6d0d8c0281a5aa784"},{"type":"text","text":"API 返回 401 了——Cookie 已经失效，需要重新登录。但系统里我刚才已经按你说的 900 股更新进去了。\n\n现在更重要的是：**你那 500 股加仓成交了，系统里有记录了，结束这个待处理。**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95874,"output":342,"cacheRead":25551,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121767,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775032607325,"responseId":"061c0c1fd4fc025373da2255befb90f0"}}
