{"type":"message","id":"025bfe9d","parentId":"692f5f54","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:55:59.889Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the log, I can see that today (2026-04-01) there were exactly 2 runs:\n1. 08:25:05 - intelligence_brief_20260401_0825.md\n2. 13:25:05 - intelligence_brief_20260401_1325.md\n\nBut Zhang Ling mentioned receiving three messages. The 08:25 one is the scheduled morning brief, and 13:25 is the noon brief. The third one - she said two were identical. \n\nWait, earlier when I ran the script at around 08:32 (during the \"马上更新数据啊\" session), I also triggered a run:\n\n\n1. 08:25:05 - 定时早报\n2. 08:32:xx - 手动触发的 0832 版（during the \"马上更新数据啊\" task, I ran `python3 scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py`）\n3. 09:26:xx - 再次运行 for the 0926 update after refreshing candidates\n\nSo there were actually three runs with timestamps around 08:25, 08:32, and 09:26. The two identical messages Zhang Ling mentioned must be the 08:25 and 08:32 versions since they both ran before the candidate refresh was complete.\n\nLooking at the actual outputs, the 08:25 run and 08:32 run produced different content since the data hadn't refreshed yet. The 09:26 run should have been the freshest version with the updated TOP3 candidates.\n\nSo the timeline shows: morning brief at 08:25 with old candidates, manual refresh at 08:32 still pulling old data, then a successful refresh at 09:26 with the new TOP3. This suggests the duplicate messages might be coming from a cron job triggering multiple times, or there were multiple push notifications sent at different intervals throughout the day. Looking at the timestamps more carefully, I realize the 08:25 briefing is the scheduled morning run, the 13:25 is the noon one, but the third message at 16:xx is the one that came after my manual refresh at 09:26. So she likely received the morning briefing, then the updated version after I refreshed the data, but something about the content or timing of these duplicates is still unclear. I think the real problem is that I accidentally triggered the script twice in quick succession - once when checking the help flag, which returned an error but still executed the generation, and then again when I meant to run it properly. That would explain why she received three notifications instead of one or two, since the push notifications go out for each run. Looking at the timing more carefully, I see the three messages were sent at 08:25, 08:32 (after my `--help` mishap triggered an extra push), and then the noon briefing at 13:25. The duplicate content suggests two of these runs used the same underlying data. I should trace back through the brief files to confirm whether 08:32 was actually identical to 08:25, or if the 13:25 version somehow got sent twice.","thinkingSignature":"cf9d3ad8c2dac497fb16ba0cfdde6b10a647b29e32f6bee40852b6f1e2544f07"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xkfwzx4ex2xf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nlogs = Path('scripts/logs')\np = logs / 'intelligence_aggregator.log'\ncontent = p.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\n# 找04-01所有运行记录\nlines = content.split('\\n')\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if '2026-04-01' in line:\n        print(f'{i}: {line}')\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xkfwzx4ex2xf_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbriefs = Path('research/reports')\nfiles = sorted(briefs.glob('intelligence_brief_20260401_*.md'))\nfor f in files:\n    print(f'{f.name}: {f.stat().st_size} bytes, mtime={f.stat().st_mtime}')\nPY","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109781,"output":938,"cacheRead":25551,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136270,"cos