{"type":"message","id":"13b82efe","parentId":"9ffb2502","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:57:04.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says \"好，修吧\" - meaning \"OK, fix it.\" I need to fix the duplicate push issue. Let me identify the specific fixes needed:\n\n1. **08:32 duplicate**: My `--help` typo triggered actual execution → need to prevent this\n2. **Evening duplicates (19:15/19:21)**: The script ran twice in the evening\n\nLet me look at the specific issues:\n\n1. For the `--help` issue: I ran `python3 scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py --help` but it seems the script doesn't have argparse-style handling and just ran anyway. I should check the script to understand why `--help` triggered execution.\n   \n2. For the evening duplicates, I need to determine whether a cron job or heartbeat triggered the script multiple times. I should check HEARTBEAT.md to see if there's a schedule that might have caused this.\n\n3. I also need to check if there's any script or cron that's set to run after market close at 19:15 and 19:21 specifically.\n\nLooking at the file timestamps, the intelligence brief was created at 19:15 and then again at 19:21, which suggests two separate triggers around that time. I should trace back to see what activated it at 19:15 in the first place.\n\nThe HEARTBEAT.md file mentions running once daily in the afternoon or evening, so that's likely one trigger. I need to dig into the cron configuration to find the other scheduled task that fired around 19:21, since those two events so close together are what caused the duplicate briefings.","thinkingSignature":"6ddcdf3d1f3aaa33f2f6a06894fce22108d3a4f39d044b67f44df7ab7420a486"},{"type":"text","text":"收到，我现在修这三条重复触发的根因。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n82w4t1f6597_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py","limit":50}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n82w4t1f6597_2","name":"e