{"type":"message","id":"3193209a","parentId":"943c53c7","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:57:25.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly. Looking at the crontab:\n\n1. `30 08 * * 1-5` - INVESTMENT_RESEARCH_BRIEF_MORNING - this runs `cron_daily_investment_research_brief.sh morning` at 08:30\n2. No explicit cron for intelligence_brief.py at 08:25\n\nBut looking at the log:\n- `08:25:05` - intelligence_brief generated (NOT from cron)\n- `08:32` - mine (duplicate)\n- `09:26` - mine (after data refresh)\n- `13:25:05` - cron investment_research_brief\n\n\n- `19:15` / `19:21` - these came from the self-improvement heartbeat or manual runs, not the cron that's scheduled for 09:34 on weekdays\n\nThe intelligence_briefs are actually triggered by the investment research mainline guard script, not by a direct intelligence_brief cron job. I see the issue now—there's no intelligence_brief.py cron at all. The 08:25 execution came from either my HEARTBEAT or the OpenClaw scheduling, while 08:32 was from my manual run, and 09:26 is still unaccounted for. The 13:25 timing aligns with the INVESTMENT_RESEARCH_BRIEF_MORNING cron that runs at 08:30 and completes by 13:25. I'm realizing the crontab output is incomplete, and the intelligence_brief.py script is likely invoked by `run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py` rather than running on its own schedule. So the triggers are: OpenClaw HEARTBEAT at 08:25, my manual run at 08:32, the script I ran at 09:26 after refreshing data, the INVESTMENT_RESEARCH_BRIEF_MORNING cron at 13:25, and two additional executions at 19:15 and 19:21 that I need to trace back to their source.\n\nLooking at the log timestamps, the HEARTBEAT at 19:15 is the most likely culprit for one of those 19:xx entries. But I'm also noticing that `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` lacks any deduplication mechanism—it'll regenerate the report even if the underlying data hasn't changed, which would explain the identical 08:25 and 08:32 briefs. The two evening runs (19:15 and 19:21) were likely triggered by my HEARTBEAT and another scheduled task like RESEARCH_MAINLINE_GUARD_NIGHT. I need to add three fixes: a check to skip regeneration if data hasn't changed, a deduplication mechanism using timestamps, and logging to prevent false --help triggers. Let me examine the aggregate script to understand how to implement these changes.","thinkingSignature":"873caa4350aa789e9c98a4288f6cec8de54856713a9eea629d557692d2f085c2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je5ekwhs2fqi_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py","offset":720,"limit":50}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je5ekwhs2fqi_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"send_feishu\\|飞书推送\\|DEDUP\\|dedup\\|last_run\\|skip\\|already\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py | head -40","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je5ekwhs2fqi_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace && grep -n \"intelligence_brief\\|aggregate_intelligence\" scripts/run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py 2>/dev/null | head -30","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":116180,"output":833,"cacheRead":25551,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":142564,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775044624360,"responseId":"061c3b101968a969a26bc2b33e4b4ed2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b7be1652","parentId":"3193209a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:57:25.852Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_je5ekwhs2fqi_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    signals  = get_quant_signals()\n    holdings = get_holdings()\n    if holdings.get(\"error\") == \"missing_selected_real_holdings_source\":\n        print(f\"[{datetime.now():%H:%M:%S}] 中止发送：missing_selected_real_holdings_source\")\n        return\n    profiles = get_paper_profiles()\n\n    print(f\"  TrendRadar: {trend_total} 条（财经 {sum(len(v) for v in trend_cats.values())} 条）\")\n    print(f\"  微博监控: {weibo.get('status', '?')} | {weibo.get('last_time', '?')}\")\n    print(f\"  量化信号: {len(signals.get('top_buy', []))} 买入候选\")\n    print(f\"  持仓: {holdings.get('count', 0)} 只\")\n    print(f\"  三盘: {list(profiles.keys())}\")\n\n    # 构建简报\n    brief = build_brief(trend_cats, weibo, signals, holdings, profiles)\n\n    # 保存\n    date_code = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M\")\n    f1 = OUTPUT_DIR / f\"intelligence_brief_{date_code}.md\"\n    f2 = OUTPUT_DIR / \"intelligence_brief_latest.md\"\n    f1.write_text(brief, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    f2.write_text(brief, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(f\"  已保存: {f1.name}\")\n    print(f\"  已更新: intelligence_brief_latest.md\")\n\n    # 飞书推送\n    print(\"\\n发送飞书预览...\")\n    ok = send_preview(trend_cats, signals)\n    print(f\"  飞书推送: {'成功' if ok else '失败'}\")\n\n    return brief\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775044645845}}
