{"type":"message","id":"34b33b04","parentId":"b2200f08","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:57:34.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The `aggregate_intelligence_brief.py` has no deduplication - it always sends to Feishu whenever it runs, regardless of whether the content changed.\n\nThe fixes needed:\n1. **Deduplication**: Before sending Feishu, compare with the previous brief. If identical, skip sending.\n2. **Minimum interval**: Don't send if less than X minutes since last send.\n3. **No direct script execution without a --dry-run guard**: The script should have a `--dry-run` or `--no-send` option for testing.\n4. **Prevent --help from executing**: The script uses `if __name__ == \"__main__\": main()` which means any invocation runs it.\n\n\n5. **No duplicate Feishu sends**: I need to add a hash check that skips sending if the brief content is identical to the previous one.\n\nLet me examine the main() function and the send_preview() function to see where the Feishu integration happens.","thinkingSignature":"a7fac2a44a905c2120494a1c232fe5e69cbd967f266d781ab62683eba1afd852"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7f7xbt626l06_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py","offset":700,"limit":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117586,"output":265,"cacheRead":25551,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775044645867,"responseId":"061c3b2661df1bb47440e0d058f78b98"}}
