{"type":"message","id":"416825f4","parentId":"1fc5c1e6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T11:58:31.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also handle the 08:32 duplicate - which was caused by my `python3 scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py --help` which accidentally ran the script. The new `--dry-run` flag solves this: my subsequent calls should use `--dry-run` for testing.\n\nAlso, let me verify the 08:32 issue was indeed my `--help` typo by looking at what I ran. Actually, I ran `python3 scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py --help` and it seemed to execute the script, not show help. This is because the script uses `if __name__ == \"__main__\"` but doesn't have argparse to handle `--help`. So `--help` was treated as a positional argument and ignored, and `main()` was called.\n \nWith my new `--dry-run` and `--no-send` flags in place, any future testing can use `--dry-run` to avoid sending notifications. The duplicate at 19:15 and 19:21 is trickier since I don't have a clear source for those runs, but the deduplication check comparing against `intelligence_brief_last_sent_hash.txt` should catch and prevent identical content from being sent twice. Let me run a quick test to confirm the new logic is functioning as expected.","thinkingSignature":"dae32fcf27e58eb4c84146ed87a228b431b53a96e01f1cf9dbfafc223e8b8e71"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sc23p7y46nms_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 scripts/aggregate_intelligence_brief.py --dry-run 2>&1 | tail -20","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120085,"output":338,"cacheRead":25551,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145974,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775044696243,"responseId":"061c3b58d2a4899ceca63bcacba46736"}}
